column5: got out for zone 20 opener friday at midnight with my brother and a friend of mine...  and the fish did not dissapoint us... we managed 13 walleye between 2 and 5 pounds in 2 hours... kept 12... we did a count on the last fish and realized he would have made it 13... so back he went.. and all the fish were caught trolling cranks and they were crushing the baits and fighting like champs!  however while cleaning them i was surprised to find that 2 of the fish were still full of eggs... ive never seen eggs in walleye in may before in my life... how about you guys??  anyways...heres that nights catch
Congrats! It's a late spring, lots will still be egg laden.

i thought it was a belly full of gobies or perch... they were some of the smaller fish we caught too...  if it was a biggun with a bloated belly i would have released it assuming it was eggs but these fish were only 2-3lbs  water is only 47-50 degrees in the LARRY right now...
VERY nice catch and a good way to start off the season....I'm guessing night trolling or am I wrong...
yup... friday from midnight till two am
Nice!!!  I can't wait to get out for some walleye.
Good start to the year. Sounds like a productive fishery in your area
Nice catch of perfect eating size fish. I am guessing they were caught in the St. Lawrence R.
Nicely done Mike    Got to love a good feed of walleyes Like Roy said, it's a late spring.... My one and only speck I caught on opener had eggs in her Great job and thanks for sharing!!! Leechman
Yup... And I cant wait till Saturday this weekend for zone 18 to open so I can fish some tribs/rivers off the st.Lawrence
Nice shooting    Cant wait to target some of those

You live near Kingston? I've been looking for someone to fish with other then my girlfriend who is always complaining about the cold. I'm up for any king of fishing although i dont have a car or boat :S
some very nice eyes from the larry 4 sure!!!!  cheers
